<simplesect kind="par"><title>Example</title><para>Taking B3LYP functional as an example. The B3LYP functional is <formula id="3">\[ E^{\rm{B3LYP}}_{\rm{xc}} = E^{\rm{LDA}}_{\rm{x}} + a_0 (E^{\rm{HF}}_{\rm{x}} - E^{\rm{LDA}}_{\rm{x}}) + a_x (E^{\rm{GGA}}_{\rm{x}} - E^{\rm{LDA}}_{\rm{x}}) + E^{\rm{LDA}}_{\rm{c}} + a_c (E^{\rm{GGA}}_{\rm{c}} - E^{\rm{LDA}}_{\rm{c}}), \]</formula> in which exchanges end with suffix <computeroutput>_x</computeroutput> and correlations end with suffix <computeroutput>_c</computeroutput>, <formula id="4">$ a_0=0.20 $</formula>, <formula id="5">$ a_x=0.72 $</formula> and <formula id="6">$ a_c=0.81 $</formula>. Only the exchanges are considered and the correlations are ignored. The GGA and LDA exchanges are viewed as the same type. Therefore, the total weights of GGA and LDA exchanges are <formula id="7">$ 1 - a_0 + a_x \times (1 - 1) = 1 - a_0 = 0.80 $</formula>, and the total weights of HF exchanges is <formula id="8">$ a_0 = 0.20 $</formula>. To construct a <computeroutput><ref refid="classlosc_1_1DFAInfo" kindref="compound">DFAInfo</ref></computeroutput> object for B3LYP functional, one should do the following <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">b3lyp<sp/>=<sp/>DFAInfo(0.80,<sp/>0.20,<sp/>&quot;B3LYP&quot;)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
